
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `lzop` baraye compress kardan (feshorde sazi) file-ha estefade mishavad, mesle `gzip` vali az algorithm-e LZO estefade mikonad ke sare'tar ast. Baaz kardan file-haye `lzop` shode ham ba in dastoor anjam mishavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `lzop -o <file>` --> 💾 Save kardan file compress shode ba name `<file>`.
    🔹 `lzop -d <file.lzo>` --> 📦 Baaz kardan file `.lzo` (decompress kardan).
    🔹 `lzop -k <file>` --> ➕ Asl-e file ra negah midarad (delete nemikonad).
    🔹 `lzop -v <file>` --> 🗣️ Namayesh etela'ate bishtar dar morede compress shodan.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ lzop file.txt

    🔹 Compress kardan `file.txt` va sakhtan `file.txt.lzo`.

    $ lzop -d file.txt.lzo

    🔹 Baaz kardan `file.txt.lzo` va sakhtan `file.txt`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ lzop -k file.txt

    🔹 `file.txt` ra compress mikonad va `file.txt.lzo` ra misazad, vali `file.txt` asl-e khodash ra negah midarad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `lzop` command is used to compress files, similar to `gzip`, but it uses the LZO algorithm, which is faster.  Decompressing `lzop` files is also done using this command.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `lzop -o <file>` --> 💾 Save the compressed file with the name `<file>`.
    🔹 `lzop -d <file.lzo>` --> 📦 Decompress the `.lzo` file.
    🔹 `lzop -k <file>` --> ➕ Keep the original file (do not delete it).
    🔹 `lzop -v <file>` --> 🗣️ Show more information about the compression process (verbose mode).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ lzop file.txt

    🔹 Compress `file.txt` and create `file.txt.lzo`.

    $ lzop -d file.txt.lzo

    🔹 Decompress `file.txt.lzo` and create `file.txt`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ lzop -k file.txt

    🔹 Compress `file.txt` and create `file.txt.lzo`, but keep the original `file.txt`.
